commit b116a7ac985f00846219473ac5c26166445a83be
Author: jeeminso <jeeminso@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Feb 18 17:22:13 2025 +0900

    Fix for unremoved empty partitions when DELETE condition contained nondeterministic functions
    
    such as `now()`. This is a regression introduced by #15924 which
    incorrectly prevented normalizing nondeterministic functions during
    WhereClauseAnalyzer.resolvePartitions().
    
    The scope of #15924 was 'Do not normalize nondeterministic functions
    during analysis' but WhereClauseAnalyzer.resolvePartitions() is not
    part of the analysis phase.
    
    (cherry picked from commit 7ec67008007e53ef9e05e7b0375fbb236585d35a)

diff --git a/docs/appendices/release-notes/5.10.2.rst b/docs/appendices/release-notes/5.10.2.rst
index f7d4908e71..e582a0c0cc 100644
--- a/docs/appendices/release-notes/5.10.2.rst
+++ b/docs/appendices/release-notes/5.10.2.rst
@@ -51,3 +51,11 @@ Fixes
 - Fixed an issue where a filter was not pushed down to the source when the
   filtered column was aliased as part of a view. This could lead to an
   unnecessary full table scan.
+
+- Fixed a regression introduced in ``5.6.5`` that caused empty partitions to be
+  left behind when ``DELETE`` condition contained a non-deterministic function
+  such as ``NOW()``, e.g.::
+
+    DELETE FROM t WHERE day < now() - INTERVAL '3 days';
+
+  where 'day' is ``TIMESTAMP`` type that is also the ``PARTITIONED BY`` column.
